# Git commits — no Cursor attribution

When the user asks to commit or push:

- Use **only**: `git commit -m "message"`
- **NEVER** use `git commit --trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor ..."`
- **NEVER** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` to commit messages
- Do **not** commit unless the user explicitly asks to commit or push
